Following the resignation of the Secretary to the Ondo State Government, Ifedayo Abegunde, on Monday, Governor Rotimi Akeredolu has announced the appointment of Temitayo Oluwatuyi as the new SSG. The governor disclosed the appointment of Oluwatuyi, popularly called Tukana, via his verified Twitter handle. The appointment, according to him, is with immediate effect. “Today, I announce the appointment of Hon. Temitayo Oluwatuyi “Tukana” as the Secretary to the State Government to resume immediately, following the resignation of Hon. Ifedayo Abegunde,” Akeredolu tweeted. Oluwatuyi was before his appointment, the Commissioner for Natural Resources in the state. 